  "why": "PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP is a solid composite electrolyte for Li-ion batteries. Results show: ionic conductivity 3.03×10^-5 S/cm at 30°C and 1×10^-4 S/cm at 50°C (Fig. 4a–b; Conclusions). Electrochemical stability window (decomposition voltage) 4.8 V (Fig. 4e). Li-ion transference number t_Li+ = 0.478 (Table 2; Fig. 6c–d). Li/PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP/Li symmetric cell operates stably for 1000 cycles at 0.1 mA/cm^2 without short circuit, indicating dendrite suppression (Fig. 7b). In quasi-solid LFP/PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP/Li cells: at 50°C and 0.5C, initial 158.06 mAh/g, 133.82 mAh/g after 200 cycles (84.66% retention) (Fig. 8b,d); at room temperature and 0.5C, initial 142.69 mAh/g, 136.41 mAh/g after 500 cycles (95.60% retention) (Fig. 9b,d). With 5 μL liquid electrolyte infiltration, conductivity increases to 3.64×10^-4 S/cm (30°C) and 7×10^-4 S/cm (50°C), and t_Li+ becomes 0.323; stability window ~4.5 V (Fig. 5; Fig. S5)."
}

